

Rule Actions:

1. to plugin actions, create an entry in the server side under:
   rulesets/<ruleset-name>/ui/actions

   example: 
   {
        name: "ADD_TAX_FEE",
	template: "add-tax-fee"
	params: {
	    lob: { datatype: "LOB", caption:"Line of Business", usevar:true },
	    account: { datatype:'string', caption:'Account', editor: "selectbarangay"},
	    amount: {datatype: "decimal", caption:"Value", expression:true }
	}
   }

   where:
      name = the name of the action
      template = the template used to render the actual rule statement
      params = parameters used for the action



2. usevar means to use variables in the condition part.
3. if editor is specified, it means you want to use a custom editor for the value. 
    you must do the ff:

    3.1. create an editor workunit type: "<name-of-editor>:actionparam-editor"
    3.2. action param must have ruleEntity and actionParam variables. 


